	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=72191><span id= >Edano</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>A massive amount of misinformation in this thread.<br><br>You need three of these gems for the caster (NEC, WIS, MAG, ENC) Kael, Thurgadin and Skyshrine robe quests.&nbsp;&nbsp;These gems are not used to aquire the Plane of Growth robe which is dropped in its fully-statted version or the Plane of Mischief robe which is quested through an immensely complex process (see this link for details: <a href="http://pub57.ezboard.com/ftheplaneofmischieffrm5.showMessage?topicID=15.topic" target=_new>http://pub57.ezboard.com/ftheplaneofmischieffrm5.showMessage?topicID=15.topic</a> ).<br><br>The silk robe that you hand in along with these gems for the Thurgadin robe can drop anywhere in Kael, although it is more common in the arena area.  The Skyshrine robe drops in the east wing(Halls of Testing) of the Temple of Veeshan.  Mobs in this wing are KoS to all and have no faction hits.  The Kael robe drops in the west wing from Claws of Veeshan faction mobs.<br><br>The gems themselves can drop in a massive number of Velious high level zones - from Velk's, to Dragon Necropolis, to Icewell, to Skyshrine, to Siren's Grotto.  They are rare and appear to drop from any high level (55+) creature.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
